                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#84rb">Fol. 84rb</locus>: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 84rb: ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ግንዘት፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ደንደራ፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ጌታው፡ አቶ፡ ኃይለ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መርሐ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note states that getaw ato Ḫaylä Śǝllase donated the book to Qǝddus Mikaʾel Dändära. It also contains a supplication for Ḫaylä Śǝllase, his wife Ṣǝllatä Muse and his children.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Erasures: fols. 8va, 53va, 55ra.&#xD;
- Erasures marked by thin lines: e.g., fols. 16rb, 65va, 67va, 77rb, 79ra.&#xD;
- Erasures marked by dashes or thin lines above and below the word: fols. 29va, 49va.&#xD;
- Corrections written interlineally: fol. 73va.&#xD;
- Omitted letters, words or passages added interlineally: e.g., fols. 12rab, 14vb, 18rb, 26rab, 32rab, 38rb.&#xD;
- The scribe used compressed script: fols. 73rb-76ra.&#xD;
- Underlined words, indicating the place where the omission written in the upper margin belongs: fol. 52va.&#xD;
- Tämälläs-sign (?) in the shape of two perpendicular lines (┤), indicating where the omission written in the upper margin belongs: fol. 56va.&#xD;
- Pen trial: fols. 9rb, 85rb, 85vb.&#xD;
- Scribbles and doodles: e.g., fols. 14r, 16r, 16v, 17v, 24r.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
